---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import { processSteps, site } from '../data/site';

const pageTitle = `About | ${site.name}`;
const pageDescription = `About ${site.founder}, why ${site.name} exists, and how each WLED installation is planned and handed off.`;
---

<SiteLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} image="/morefancy.jpeg">
	<main class="page-shell about-page">
		<section class="page-hero narrow-hero">
			<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
			<h1>{site.name} is how I turn WLED from a hobbyist tool into a finished install.</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				I am {site.founder}, and I build lighting installs that look clean, feel customized, and stay easy
				to use after the install is over. What started as building out my own spaces turned into helping
				family, clients, and friends light houses, cabinets, shelves, offices, and holiday displays.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="about-grid">
			<article class="card prose-card">
				<h2>Why I started doing this</h2>
				<p>
					A lot of LED setups either look unfinished, feel too technical, or get stuck doing one thing well.
					I like building systems that solve all three problems at once: they are mounted cleanly, they feel
					good in the space, and they stay flexible because WLED is underneath everything.
				</p>
				<p>
					That means one install can shift between subtle everyday lighting, bold holiday scenes, team colors,
					and event presets without tearing anything out later.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="card prose-card">
				<h2>What the customer experience looks like</h2>
				<p>
					The controller box is usually placed on the side of the house or in the garage so power and access
					stay practical. From there, wiring follows the mounted channel, the system joins Wi-Fi, and the
					lighting can sync with other zones if you want everything moving together.
				</p>
				<p>
					I also help with the first layer of presets, schedules, and app setup, and I provide a remote so
					using the lights does not depend on having your phone out all the time.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="section-block">
			<div class="section-heading">
				<p class="eyebrow">Approach</p>
				<h2>Every install is planned around the finished look and the daily experience.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="steps-grid">
				{processSteps.map((step) => (
					<article class="card step-card">
						<h3>{step.title}</h3>
						<p>{step.description}</p>
					</article>
				))}
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
	.about-page {
		padding-bottom: 5rem;
	}
	.narrow-hero {
		max-width: 54rem;
	}
	.about-grid,
	.steps-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1.25rem;
	}
	.prose-card h2,
	.step-card h3 {
		margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
	}
	.section-block {
		padding-top: 2.5rem;
	}
	.section-heading {
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}
	@media (max-width: 780px) {
		.about-grid,
		.steps-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
